results.definition: employment for performers or performing groups that lasts for a limited period of time
examples: the play had bookings throughout the summer

results.definition: the act of reserving (a place or passage) or engaging the services of (a person or group)
examples: wondered who had made the booking
Her agent had booked her for several concerts in Tokyo

results.definition: arrange for and reserve (something for someone else) in advance
examples: reserve me a seat on a flight
The agent booked tickets to the show for the whole family
please hold a table at Maxim's

results.definition: record a charge in a police register
examples: The policeman booked her when she tried to solicit a man
